
* Changes in jai 0.3

** New features

Allow -u and -j together to specify only one sandbox to unmount.

Sandboxes now mount a writable /dev/shm (accessible outside the
sandbox under /run/jai/$USER/tmp/.shm/$JAI_JAIL).

--conf?, and --dir! options, to ignore configuration files that don't
exist and to create missing directories outside the sandbox.

Added the --script and --script? options to assemble a startup script
that can be sourced in the bash line specified by command.

Added the -r, --rdir, and --rdir? options to export directories
read-only.

** Portability changes

jai now compiles with g++14, despite only partial range support.

Removed dependencies on libmount, acl, and pkg-config to make it
easier to compile.

jai now compiles with clang libc++ (despite the lack of
std::move_only_function).
